g.text: Suggestion: Be honest. He's not grilling you, he just wants to know. Ask if he's ever wanted to take it too.
You: "It has no effect on my performance, I just take it to feel good."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Hmh." He lets out a little pensive hum... "That's what I thought. Let's go?"
Rhetoric: There is little condescension in his phrasing, more measured curiosity.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Hmh." He lets out a little pensive hum. "Thought so. Let's go?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Hmh." He lets out a little pensive hum. "Thought so. Let's go?"
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant *tries* to keep his eyes on the door, but the Preptide bottle sounds like a rattlesnake -- it's basically a percussion instrument that you're stuffing into your pocket.
You: Search for the Preptide again.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Mhm," the lieutenant nods. "She certainly had her priorities straight when she was packing."
Kim Kitsuragi: "An opioid receptor antagonist. It's used for diamorphine overdoses."
Inland Empire: And your chest swells with pride -- look! It's made right here in Revachol, by Saint-Batiste, a proud Revacholian pharmaceutical company with great *traditions*!
You: "I was kinda hoping the *gift* would be in here."
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant does not pursue the subject further, looking out the bathroom window instead.
Empathy: This toothbrush belongs to someone who doesn't give a damn about her teeth.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Right. Thank you for this information." He seems satisfied. "Should we go?"
Cuno: "Smart chick." The kid nods. "Cuno never leaves shit behind either. Cuno's a pro."
You: "I understand it's unbecoming but if I don't perform this job well I am nothing. It's the price I pay."
Logic: Probably Garte's work. After she was arrested.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Interesting. That's used for diamorphine overdoses..." The lieutenant nods -- then looks at the door.
You: "Honesty, it makes me the detective I am. Have you thought of taking it too?"
Drama: It's not insincere. He's actually giving it thought.
You: "Looking like a beast in heat is a serious downside, yes."
Kim Kitsuragi: "There's always a price..." He looks out the window.
Electrochemistry: Who cares, man? Who cares what the stiff thinks? Here comes the afterburner! Just put it in your sweaty little hand now...
Cuno: "Nah, pig..." the kid says looking around like a young wolf. "That'd been too easy. Let's keep looking."
Medicine Cabinet: This medicine cabinet is full of wares -- sheets of pills haphazardly stacked one on top of the other. There's also a toothbrush somewhere in there.
You: Just take it in plain sight.
You: Is there something more interesting here?
Kim Kitsuragi: "Right." He seems satisfied with your answer. "I can see how that can be useful."
Medicine Cabinet: Pharmaceuticals line the shelves. Sheet upon sheet and pill bottle next to pill bottle: acetylic acid, APAP, eye drops, blood thinners...
You: "It keeps me going -- in the short run."
Reaction Speed: You could say he's on the *lookout*.
Authority: Yes, take it... and then dispose of it! This den of narcomania cannot be allowed stand!
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant looks toward the door as if he didn't see you pilfer that sweet Preptide.
Electrochemistry: ...nothing of note. The further you look the more arcane it gets. You don't know what the rest of this stuff does.
You: "There's quite the collection in here."
Encyclopedia: NACRA? This is used to treat opioid overdoses. Always handy to have around.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I was just curious. Anyway let's go."
Reaction Speed: So... the good lieutenant was looking for an edge, was he?
Electrochemistry: Who cares, man? Who cares what the stiff thinks? You got it. Here comes the afterburner! Just put it in your sweaty little hand now...
You: "What are you talking about? I don't take amphetamine, don't be *ludicrous*!"
"What are you talking about? I'm not a narcomaniac, don't be *ludicrous*!"

Electrochemistry: A bright orange bottle with PREPTIDE stamped on it. In sunny, happy letters! Jackpot, baby! That's the stuff you're looking for! Your palms begin to sweat just holding that little plastic container.
Medicine Cabinet: Feels like gold in your hands. Light and precious.
You: Pick it up -- but secretly.
Perception (Sight): Wow. That's unbelievably orange. *Anyone* can see that. It's practically *effervescent*!
Kim Kitsuragi: "I always took you for more of a drunk than a chemical abuser," he says as though it's self-evident. "Anyway."
"I always took you for more of a drunk than a chemical abuser, lieutenant-yefreitor," he says as though its self-evident. "Should we go?"
Medicine Cabinet: The medicine cabinet has been cleaned out. Nothing remains, not one pill or bottle.
The medicine cabinet is empty. Not even a toothbrush.

Medicine Cabinet: Pill bottles rattle like bones as you search the cabinet: paracetamol, histaperidol, something in a foreign language you can't read... Behind them: an unusually shaped nasal spray. Its label reads 'NACRA'.
Perception (Smell): It's clean of chemical odours too. Just some dried toothpaste on the handle.
You: "Lieutenant, I also see a brand called 'Preptide.'"
Medicine Cabinet: Among some foreign -- probably Messinian, or Gottwaldian -- marked red blister packs you find... what *do* you find? This is going to take a little know-how.
You: "Nah, man, the jaw grinding and the sweating -- that's the best part. Shows the medicine is working."
Interfacing: You dropped it. Smack dab in the middle of the floor! There it is -- orange as the midsummer evening's sun, or the lieutenant's bomber jacket.
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant glances at the rows of pills -- then at the door.
Medicine Cabinet: You're just talking to your reflection in the cabinet doors now... Things are not good with you.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Of course you were." He nods. "How does that work anyway?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Amphetamine -- does it make you a better detective?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Doesn't the... pupils and the gurning jaw, the sweating... doesn't it become tiring after a while?"
Electrochemistry: There it is, the orange sun wearing blister pack. You feel almost *nostalgic* for it.
Perception (Sight): But not for scrubbing blood off tiles -- or anything else interesting, it seems.
You: What's so exciting about this orange bottle?
What was so exciting about the orange bottle?
Interfacing: He did, though. He totally did and now he thinks less of you. Should have kept it *sub rosa*.
Medicine Cabinet: This medicine cabinet is stocked with drugs, plus an old toothbrush, and...
Kim Kitsuragi: "I thought so." He seems satisfied with the answer. "Should we go?"
Electrochemistry: The fuck are you waiting for, let's get super fucking PREPPIE!!!
Pain Threshold: The beating he took must be more serious than he lets on.
You: "It gives me fiery visions. A window into the heart of things."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes, but... did you know you don't *have* radiation sickness?"
Electrochemistry: Feels so sleek and beautiful -- you got it! Here comes the afterburner! Time to become a super-detective again, Harry! Just put it in your sweaty little hand now...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Right. I'll give it some thought." He seems satisfied with your answer. "Should we go?"
Medicine Cabinet: It's been used. Quite a lot.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Preptide -- a euphemism for pharmaceutical amphetamine. Prescription speed."
Kim Kitsuragi: "It may be -- but I asked if it makes you better at your work?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Maybe I should?" He lets out a little pensive hum, rubbing his shoulder...

Electrochemistry: It's speed, man! Just what you were looking for. They call it *dextroamphetamine* and talk about psychological disorders, but what we're seeing here is some scientifically advanced trucker speed!
Interfacing: Silently the bottle slides into your palm, then -- as you turn -- into your pocket.
Interfacing: You dropped it. Smack dab in the middle of the floor! There it is -- orange as the midsummer evening's sun.
You: "Yes, that does sound dangerous now that I think about it."
Authority: Filthy narco! And look -- it's made right here in Revachol, by Saint-Batiste. A disgraceful pharmaceutical company attempting to lure people into the gutter. You should destroy it!
Kim Kitsuragi: "Anything of note?" he asks in a lowered voice.
You: "I'm too high on pyrholidon to notice. Before you ask -- pyrholidon is used for radiation sickness."
Medicine Cabinet: The cabinet is cleaned out, emptied.
You: "Better? No. It makes me worse."
